The paper deals with developing a Bayesian Poisson matrix factorization model for forming recommendations from sparse user behavior data. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with developing a machine learning model for recommendation. The second likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as recommendation systems are often used in information retrieval applications. The third likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses a scalable algorithm for matrix factorization. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as recommendation systems are often used in social networks. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with developing an AI-based recommendation system.
